data.title: Lewis-Clark State College Athletics
data.meta_description: Karina Davila - JUNIOR: First team All-Frontier Conference selection…Finished in the top-10 in all six tournaments including two top five’s…Averaged 80.2 strokes
data.text:
JUNIOR: First team All-Frontier Conference selection…Finished in the top-10 in all six tournaments including two top five’s…Averaged 80.2 strokes per round over 10 rounds…Recorded a pair of runner-up finishes, Warriors Invite and the Frontier Conference Championship…Had the lowest round of the Championship with a 74, even par for the course.

SOPHOMORE: Frontier Conference All-League first team selection...Third in Frontier Conference and second on LCSC with per round average of 75.5 in eight rounds of league action...Low round of 73 in conference play...Tied for fifth overall and second on LCSC at Frontier Conference Championships...Tied for 51st at NAIA Nationals.

FRESHMAN: All-Frontier Conference second team selection in her first collegiate season…Average of 81 was fourth on Warrior roster in nine rounds of league play…Fired a 75 at Westminster Invitational for low round of season.

HIGH SCHOOL: Had a trio of top three finishes in the South Conference Tournament while playing at Centro Educativo Jean Piaget…As a sophomore, was a member of the Mexican team at the Optimist World championship and placed second in the National Junior Partners Tournament…Took third at the National Team championship in 2009…Also played soccer and volleyball

PERSONAL: Born Sept. 1, 1993 to Carlos Davila and Susana Castillo in Fortin, Veracruz, Mexico…Currently lives in Cordoba, Veracruz, Mexico and has a sister, Karla, and a brother, Carlos…Hobbies include sports, music and hanging out…Plans to major in Sports Administration

FAVORITE FOOD: Chinese food, pizza, Mexican food

FAVORITE SPORT OTHER THAN : Volleyball and soccer

FAVORITE MOVIES: The Notebook, A Walk to Remember, 13 Going On 30

FAVORITE TV SHOW: The Big Bang Theory

FAVORITE PRO ER: Lorena Ochoa

MOST INFLUENTIAL PERSON: My dad

ONE WORD TO DESCRIBE KARINA: Fun

WHY I CHOSE LCSC: Athletic and bachelor programs

GOAL AFTER GRADUATION: Develop sport facilities projects and coach

DRIVER: Nike Convert

WOODS: TaylorMade

IRONS: Titleist

FAVORITE CLUB: Driver
